ght choreographer for other actors such as Jackie Chan.\nHung is one of the pivotal figures who spearheaded the Hong Kong New Wave movement of the 1980s, helped reinvent the martial arts genre and started the vampire-like jiangshi genre. He is widely credited with assisting many of his compatriots, giving them their starts in the Hong Kong film industry, by casting them in the films he produced, or giving them roles in the production crew.\nBoth Sammo Hung and Jackie Chan were often addressed as \"Dai Goh”, meaning Big Brother, until the filming of Project A, which featured both actors. As Hung was the eldest of the kung fu \"brothers\", and the first to make a mark on the industry, he was given the nickname “Dai Goh Dai\", meaning, Big, Big Brother, or Biggest Big Brother.\n\n", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T13:01:04.582791+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 3058, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sammo_Hung"}], "uuid": "7d8088af-a00d-45f6-bdee-92929bbdda35", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "28512", "external_references": [{"id": 12983, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q311219"}, {"id": 12984, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "9453057"}, {"id": 12985, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no97058057"}, {"id": 12986, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no97058057"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:32:34.923663+10:00"}, {"id": 31284, "name": "VPRO", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 908905, "title": "Whoever says the truth shall die : A film about Pier Paolo Pasolini", "work_id": 89349, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2277059, "title": "The Prisoner", "work_id": 93989, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2277092, "title": "The Third force", "work_id": 93988, "role": "produc